    "category": "Savings",
    "content": "Saving money does not start with big sacrifices. It starts with awareness. Track all your expenses for at least 7 days, including small purchases like coffee or delivery fees. Once you see where your money actually goes, choose one category where you can realistically reduce spending by 5–10%. The key is consistency. Automate your savings so a small amount is transferred to savings immediately after you receive your income. This removes the need for discipline and makes saving automatic."
