    "category": "Savings",
    "content": "An emergency fund is money set aside for unexpected situations such as medical expenses, urgent repairs, or temporary loss of income. Without it, people often rely on high-interest loans or credit cards. A good long-term goal is to save 3 to 6 months of essential expenses. You don’t need to build it overnight. Start small, contribute regularly, and keep the fund separate from your daily spending account."
