    "category": "Savings",
    "content": "Paying yourself first means saving before you spend, not after. Instead of saving whatever is left at the end of the month, treat savings as a mandatory expense. Even a small fixed amount creates momentum. Over time, this habit builds financial security and reduces stress, because saving is no longer dependent on willpower."
